category = 3
text = "What decides political strength is majority, and majority gets tossed around the many parties often. As much as this shows instability, it shows more on how the population of Befre votes reactionarily in elections. The parties therefore adapted over history to be more maleable, something that was not the case in early parliment. Yet still the 3 main parties keep ideals alive, even if they may have to adapt them to please the people. Despite there being many parties, many do not set off the ground and 90% of seats tend to be one of 3 parties.

The EDP is the party that had the majority in the previous term, they only lost it a year ago to the PPP. The Economic Dependence Party consists of economists and ex-business owners who believe that the most important thing to this country is Economic Growth. They believe that isolation is not positive for the country anymore, as there is a massive gain to be gotten from opening trading borders to sell products previously not available in the global market. Simultaneosly, this also increases the Befre peoples standard of living as there will be more money in the Befre economy to be spent on them. Typically the EDP is not liked within poor areas of the country as the party does mention helping poverty, they mainly want the country to grow, something that the private business owners will benefit more from. It also does not help that the party started off in a rural area with intentions on helping poverty, and has diverted a far way since.

Next up is the BIP or the Befre Independence Party. The party is made up of what you would typically expect from a political party. Led by Lukas Arrgrin, ex-CEO of Befre's largest hotel chain, BIP have not won majority in the 10 years, mainly because their last term was during the Assassination of Juilies the Paragen. [The Black Heart Gang]'s killing of the kings brother was surprisingly linked with the party and it was even more suspicious because the BIP had feuds with the king over opening borders at the time. The main focus of the party is on staying isolationist and not taking resources from other nations. They often want to keep museums untouchable and limit access to research on the Icy Hollows from other countries, especially to those in Volin. This party is quite unpopular with the younger and economically-aware population meanwhile winning over the older and more royalist voters.

Lastly, there is the PPP or the Peoples Progressive Party. They are currently in majority, and did so by having the largest majority vote in 30 years and second of all time. The party is led by Pam Erogr, a celebrity who is known for her extreme philanthropy, donating over half her earnings to charities. The PPP is known for their policies surrounding people and their benefits, is the most friendly with the Blue Caps as her and Renata were friends in the Tompel Univesity and highlight the issues in the system like the poverty and taxation rates. The largest concern for the PPP is the lack of effectiveness with foreign affairs like trade and the fact that their main aim, to make \"heinously rich\" companies public, is against constitution seeing as other party members disagree and it would cause utter turmoil if a different party won next term."
id = 27
name = "Political Parties"
